{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17625276","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17625276"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T16:22:50+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T16:22:50+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17015"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17015","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17015"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9705"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75955"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"9705","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/9705"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17015"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61456"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"5326"},{"type":"tags","id":"5338"},{"type":"tags","id":"5346"},{"type":"tags","id":"5528"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"22841"},{"type":"contributions","id":"22849"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75955","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/75955"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EClimate change represents a significant threat to global public health through various direct and indirect mechanisms.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes a direct health impact of climate change?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Changes in vector-borne disease distribution","Mental health effects from economic instability","Increased heat-related illness and mortality","Population displacement due to rising sea levels","Reduced crop yields leading to malnutrition"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eincreased heat-related illness and mortality\u003C/strong\u003E represents a direct health impact of climate change, as it is immediately caused by rising global temperatures. Heat stress can lead to dehydration, heat exhaustion, heat stroke, and exacerbation of cardiovascular conditions.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options represent indirect health impacts:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EChanges in vector-borne disease distribution\u003C/strong\u003E occurs through altered ecological conditions that affect disease vectors and their habitats.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EReduced crop yields leading to malnutrition\u003C/strong\u003E results from changes in rainfall patterns and temperature effects on agricultural productivity.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPopulation displacement due to rising sea levels\u003C/strong\u003E represents a secondary effect of climate change that primarily impacts coastal communities through gradual environmental changes.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMental health effects from economic instability\u003C/strong\u003E develops through downstream social and economic consequences of climate-related disruptions to society.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EDirect health impacts of climate change are those immediately caused by environmental changes, while indirect impacts occur through intermediate pathways involving ecological or societal systems.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Climate change causes direct health impacts through extreme weather events, heat stress, and air pollution.","Indirect health effects of climate change include altered disease patterns, food insecurity, 